title: BREAKING: Julian Assange Agrees to U.S. Extradition Under ONE Condition…
text:
07:06pm January 12, 2017   
Barack Obama may commute the 35-year sentence of traitor Bradley Manning (who leaked classified info) before leaving office. 
If he does this, WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange will agree to be extradited to the United States. 
Interesting, to say the least. If Obama grants Manning clemency Assange will agree to US extradition despite clear unconstitutionality of DoJ case https://t.co/MZU30SlfGK 
From Daily Caller : 
WikiLeaks announced Thursday that its founder Julian Assange has agreed to be extradited to the United States if President Barack Obama grants clemency to incarcerated former U.S. Army soldier Chelsea Manning. 
Manning — then known as “Bradley” — was court-martialed in 2013 for passing nearly 1 million classified documents to WikiLeaks in 2012. 
… 
Rumors that Manning was on the sort list to receive a commuted sentence from President Obama first broke on Wednesday. 
Assange has been holed up in the Ecuadorian Embassy in London since 2012. 
The Obama administration currently has an ongoing investigation into Assange and WikiLeaks. 
Let’s hear your thoughts.
